author: @vandarik5766
text: one thing about WoW in this regard is that it was actually cool when we had professions that had quests built around them and better items were gated behind them so it would feel like you were going on this epic quest to be the best Smith or whatever but Blizzard alway drops the ball in professions and doesn't go all out like they should and open that up and build the world adventuring and interaction around it. World quests were kind of a let down classic wow quests for professions were cool and so was some of the stuff they did in WoD and Legion. What would be even better is having professions craftables be different based on class and have unique properties that make them good for their class almost replacing artifact or systems or whatever like warrior paladins and death knights could craft different gear only available to their individual class that provided unique properties only to them but make this the same idea for every single profession that way the content is immersive but also allow them to craft other items that allow the players to make reasonable in game currency and have real value in ingame content and I feel in shadowlands legendary items had some elements of this idea but they should really take it further minus the grueling downsides of farming for those blasted legendary's. Now I'm not saying you shouldn't farm but I think complex recipes that make you adventure the game and clear content to acquire materials is the ideal way to do things and ultimately make it hard for bots to farm the most valuable resources reducing their power in the in game economy. They have to do something about the zombie accounts even if it means rigging the game against them. I hope the government shuts down the wow token so blizzard has to actually take responsibility for all the hackers that made it necessary in the first place and honestly the in game economy is ruined for the new casual player  you have to buy wow tokens in retail now  you have to and that is messed up why would anyone want to come play this game with the expectation they will have to dump large sums of money in order to have any real success or enjoyment? What are these developers and publishers thinking?

author: @Diddyparty776
text: Playboi Carti isn't just a rapper; he's a cultural disruptor. His impact on modern hip-hop is undeniable  pushing boundaries with his experimental sound and unique fashion sense. Carti's music isn't always about lyrical complexity; it's about creating a vibe  an atmosphere. His use of ad-libs  distorted beats  and repetitive hooks is intentional  crafting a sonic landscape that's both hypnotic and chaotic. This distinctive approach has spawned countless imitators  but none have quite captured the same magic.  A huge part of Carti's appeal is his "aura." He's cultivated an enigmatic persona  rarely giving interviews and maintaining a strong sense of mystery. This carefully constructed image  combined with his undeniable charisma  makes him a captivating figure. His influence extends beyond music  shaping fashion trends and inspiring a generation of artists to embrace individuality and experimentation. Carti embodies a rebellious spirit  constantly reinventing himself and defying expectations.  Ultimately  whether or not you consider Playboi Carti the GOAT is subjective. But there's no denying his impact. He's a trendsetter  an innovator  and a true original. His willingness to take risks and his dedication to his unique artistic vision have solidified his place as one of the most influential artists of his generation. He's not just making music; he's creating a world  and people are drawn to that.
